 BY ADEMETO ADELEKAN, BENIN UNKNOWN gunmen, on Sunday morning, kidnapped the Public Relations Officer of the Nigerian Immigration Service, Edo State Command, Mrs. Bridget Esene. Esene was said to have been abducted from Church around Iqueniro, off Agbor Road. Our correspondent gathered that the NIS spokesperson was dragged out of her car and whisked away in the abductorsâ€™ vehicle to an unknown destination. Sources, however, said her car had been recovered but that the kidnappers had yet to contact the Immigration Service or family members for ransom. Eyewitnesses said the gunmen drove towards the Benin-Auchi Road. Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Chidi Nwabuzor, could not be reached as of the time of filing this report.  